title: Lower BOO Single Stake emissions with release of Buyback BOO staking?
body:
The BOO Single Stake was originally planned to run for ~13 weeks. At the time of presenting this proposal, there is ~7 weeks remaining in Single Stake.

If emissions are lowered, the Single Stake end time would be extended.

| Lower Emissions By | Approx Time Extended |
|:------------------:|:--------------------:|
|         50%        |        3 weeks       |
|         30%        |        2 weeks       |
|         15%        |        1 week        |
|         0%         |         None         |

The emission lowering would be enacted at the same moment the new Buyback BOO single staking pool goes live. Lowering emissions lowers inflation at the same time buy pressure is introduced with buybacks.

In this vote, you can select *multiple* choices. Select all the choices you support for your vote.
